<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,474,323,349]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[491,722,324,349]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Ischnochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[491,722,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ischnochiton pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs from Tumbes, 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1078,324,350]" name="Peru" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Perú</collectingCountry>
, southwards to the Atlantic coast of Tierra del Fuego, 
<collectingCountry box="[711,832,364,390]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. It is also known from offshore of the Chilean Juan Fernández Archipelago (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas" box="[733,1036,404,430]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1994) Monograph of living chitons. (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) 5, Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Ischnochitoninae (concluded) Callistoplacinae; Mopaliidae; Additions to Volumes 1 - 4, E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 402 pp." type="book chapter" year="1994">
Kaas &amp; Van Belle 
<number box="[973,1036,404,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Reid" pageId="8" pageNumber="26" refString="Reid, D. G. &amp; Osorio, C. (2000) The shallow-water marine Mollusca of the Estero Elefantes and Laguna San Rafael, southern Chile. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, London (Zoology), 66 (2), 109 - 146." type="journal article" year="2000">
Reid &amp; Osorio (
<number box="[361,425,444,470]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[447,536,444,469]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Ischnochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[447,536,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">I. pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the underside of stones and other hard substrata from the intertidal zone down to 
<quantity box="[540,602,484,510]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="90.0">90 m</quantity>
, with a depth preference around 
<quantity box="[982,1070,484,510]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="17.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="5.0">5–30 m</quantity>
in fjord areas. This is supported by our study and we speculate that 
<taxonomicName box="[800,1022,524,549]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Ischnochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[800,1022,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ischnochiton pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less tolerant of salinity fluctuations and therefore lives below the halocline.
</paragraph>
